score.explanation: Your Wi-Fi network is performing well, but there may be some congestion affecting performance.
score.trend_summary: Since last scan: download improved, upload improved, ping stayed the same, networks stayed the same.

latest_report.diagnosis: Your network is experiencing congestion, especially on the 2.4GHz band. Random dropouts can occur due to interference from neighboring networks.

performance.interpretation: Download speeds are strong, while upload speeds could be improved. The ping is acceptable for online activities.

problems: High congestion on 2.4GHz band causing interference.
Multiple neighboring networks operating on the same channels.
Inadequate upload speed for potential smart home devices.
fixes: Switch the 2.4GHz channel to channel 1 for less congestion.
Change the 5GHz channel to 149 for a more stable connection.
Ensure router placement is optimized; moving it closer to the center of the home could reduce dropouts.
Consider enabling Band Steering to help devices connect to the optimal frequency.
Review connected devices for bandwidth usage, especially during peak times.
Educate family members on bandwidth-heavy activities during non-peak times.
